meetingNotes.notes: Client presented with increased anxiety this week. Discussed coping strategies including deep breathing exercises and mindfulness techniques. Homework assigned: practice daily mindfulness for 10 minutes.
Session focused on trauma processing using EMDR techniques. Client showed good tolerance and engagement. Plan to continue trauma work in next session with additional grounding exercises.
Family dynamics discussion revealed additional stressors. Introduced boundary-setting techniques and communication skills. Client motivated to practice assertiveness in family interactions.

Significant progress noted in mood regulation. Client reported using CBT techniques successfully during a challenging work situation. Continue current treatment plan with focus on thought challenging.
Substance use recovery focus. Client maintained sobriety for 2 weeks. Discussed triggers and relapse prevention strategies. Connected with sponsor and AA meetings.

posts.content: I wanted to share that I've been making small progress lately. It's not always easy, but I'm learning to celebrate the little victories. Thank you all for being such a supportive community.

posts.title: Grateful for this community

reviews.title: Life-changing experience
reviews.content: The therapy sessions with Dr. Lisa have been exactly what I needed. They have a wonderful way of helping me understand my thoughts and emotions while providing practical tools for improvement.

reviews.title: Compassionate and effective
reviews.content: I was hesitant about therapy at first, but Dr. Michael made me feel at ease from our very first session. Their expertise and genuine care have helped me work through challenges I've been facing for years.
